&lt;p&gt;Saildrone is seeking a Mechanical Engineer II to join our Hardware Engineering Team. Reporting to the VP of Hardware Engineering, you will be a hands-on contributor responsible for the design, prototyping, and validation of electromechanical systems. We are looking for a technical problem-solver who can bridge the gap between digital design and physical hardware, moving fluidly from CAD to the machine shop to ensure our autonomous vehicles are robust and mission-ready.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE TEAM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Hardware Engineering Team develops and deploys Saildrone’s autonomous ocean systems. We focus on delivering reliable, scalable hardware for maritime domain awareness, operating in a high-stakes national security and defense environment. This role sits at the heart of our hardware execution, directly impacting the durability and manufacturability of our vehicles and sensor payloads.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the design and development of complex electromechanical parts, assemblies, and the specialized production tooling/weld fixtures required to build them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform hands-on assembly and fabrication tasks, including drilling, manual machining, bonding, and basic welding to iterate on designs quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct engineering analyses (hand calculations, fluid systems, and thermodynamics) and execute physical validation testing to verify design integrity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create detailed 3D CAD models (NX), dimensioned 2D drawings, and maintain accurate Bills of Materials (BOM) through the product lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Electrical Engineering to review harness designs and ensure seamless mechanical integration of sensors and circuits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work directly with fabrication shops and contract manufacturers to resolve production blockers and improve manufacturability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to and contribute to Saildrone’s drafting and engineering standards to ensure high-quality, repeatable results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor for design defects or manufacturing risks, taking proactive action to resolve issues before they impact schedule or performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
