&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Professional Representation: &lt;/strong&gt;Act as a brand ambassador for Saildrone, maintaining high levels of self-awareness and professionalism during all interactions with clients and internal colleagues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Continuous Improvement: &lt;/strong&gt;Proactively assess current workflows, in-field assembly procedures, and vehicle designs to provide feedback that increases safety, consistency, and overall efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&g

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;THE COMPANY&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Saildrone is a maritime defense company and the global leader in autonomous unmanned surface vehicles (USVs). With more ocean miles and real-world operational experience than any USV manufacturer or operator, Saildrone maintains active, combat-deployed systems supporting national security and force projection around the world, 24/7/365.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Saildrone’s manufacturing and R&amp;amp;D headquarters are located in Alameda, CA, with business development and sales operations in Washington, DC, and deployment hubs in Europe and the Middle East. By combining proven autonomous operations, edge computing, advanced sensing, renewable power, and the most advanced and robust unmanned surface technology on the planet, Saildrone is shaping how the Navy of the future operates. Join a fast-moving, mission-driven team at the forefront of maritime security and autonomous innovation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE POSITION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Saildrone is seeking a Vice President of Software to join our Software organization. Reporting directly to the CEO, you will play a critical role in defining and executing Saildrone’s software strategy and delivering mission-critical software systems that power autonomous maritime operations. You will shape the technical direction of the company while ensuring reliable, scalable, and secure software across autonomy, data, cloud, and customer-facing platforms supporting defense, government, and commercial missions. We are looking for a senior technology leader who creates clarity from complexity, sets technical direction under uncertainty, and drives execution in high-stakes operational environments, balancing long-term strategy with rigorous delivery of production-ready systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE TEAM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Software organization is responsible for the systems that power Saildrone’s autonomous maritime platform, spanning onboard autonomy and embedded systems, cloud infrastructure, data pipelines, machine learning, cybersecurity, and customer-facing applications. We are focused on delivering secure, scalable, and resilient software systems that enable persistent maritime awareness, autonomous operations, and mission-critical capabilities in national security and defense environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Execution:&lt;/strong&gt; Define and execute a multi-year software strategy and roadmap that directly supports Saildrone’s defense, government, and commercial mission objectives, while meeting reliability, security, and delivery standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;End-to-End Ownership:&lt;/strong&gt; Be accountable for the full software lifecycle across autonomy, embedded systems, data, cloud, and application platforms supporting autonomous maritime operations, including architecture, development, deployment, and sustained operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Reliability &amp;amp; Scale:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure defense-grade reliability, security, and performance of software systems, maintaining production readiness for global maritime deployments and mission-critical use cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Delivery:&lt;/strong&gt; Work closely with Hardware, Product, Security, Operations, and TPM teams to align priorities, de-risk dependencies, and deliver tightly integrated systems that translate technical capabilities into operational mission outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engineering Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt; Drive consistent adoption of modern engineering practices, including automated testing, observability, and security-by-design, to institutionalize predictable, high-quality software delivery for autonomous and defense-critical systems.&lt;/li&gt
